## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// ❌ Bug — stops one index short, skips the last item
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// ✅ Fix — iterates over all indices
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Single change needed:** Remove the `- 1` from the loop condition.

**Why it broke:** For an array of length `n`, valid indices are `0` through `n-1`. The condition `i < n - 1` only reaches index `n-2`, permanently skipping the last element. This affects all non-empty arrays — even a single-element array returns `[]` instead of the processed value.

**Verification:** All 4 existing tests in `tests/utils.test.ts` (empty array, 1 item, 2 items, 3 items) will pass after the fix with `npx vitest run`.
